Reliance Communications, Sugar Makers: India Equity Preview

-- B y   R a j e s h   K u m a r   S i n g h
-- 
2011-03-22T01:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/reliance-communications-sugar-makers-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
39.76, or 0.2 percent, to 17,839.05. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on
the National Stock Exchange declined 0.2 percent to 5,364.75.
The BSE 200 Index decreased 0.2 percent to 2,205.45.  Sugar Makers: India may allow exports of 200,000 metric
tons of sugar at a meeting of lawmakers scheduled for today.
Shares of  Bajaj Hindusthan Ltd. (BJH)  , the nation’s largest
producer, rose less than 0.1 percent to 68.65 rupees.  Balrampur
Chini Mills Ltd. (BRCM)  , the second biggest, rose less than
0.1 percent to 70.5 rupees.  Reliance Communications Ltd. (RCOM)  : The company
controlled by billionaire Anil Ambani was downgraded to
“underperform” from “outperform” at Macquarie Research by
equity analyst Unmesh Sharma. The 12-month target price is 87
rupees per share. The stock declined 1.6 percent to 102.9 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
